 The Kwara State Police Command, on Sunday, confirmed the killing of a suspected cultist in Ilorin and arrest of three others. A statement by the Police Public Relations Officer in the state, SP Ajayi Okasami, read that the arrest followed the killing of another suspected cultist by a rival cult group along Emir Road, Ilorin, on Saturday. “A report of sporadic shootings by suspected cultists was received by the Divisional Police Headquarters, Surulere, Ilorin, around Total Filling Station, on February 5, at about 9:35pm. “On arrival at the scene, detectives from both the division and the anti-cultism team dispatched by the commissioner of police were faced with an unidentified body of a young man lying in the pool of his blood, having been shot by suspected cultists. “Three suspects were arrested while one motorcycle and one tricycle used by the suspected cultists were also recovered. “The commissioner of police, Tuesday Assayomo, has ordered a discreet investigation into the case and all other cult-related cases in the state,” it read. The statement added that the CP ordered a 24-hour aggressive patrol of Ilorin metropolis, while also soliciting for the cooperation of everyone in the effort at ensuring peace. “Parents and guardians are advised to monitor the activities of their wards and ask their children questions when in doubt of their dealings. “The CP reiterated his commitment to ensuring safety and security of lives and property of citizens and residents of Kwara,” it read. (NAN). 